          ],
          [
            86.0,
            1241.0
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "In this section, we trained six shadow models to facilitate the attack. We focus on unconditional diffusion models and test on CIFAR-10 and ImageNet datasets.",
        "block_bbox": [
          85,
          1257,
          597,
          1332
        ],
        "block_id": 12,
        "block_order": 5,
        "group_id": 12,
        "global_block_id": 175,
        "global_group_id": 175,
        "block_polygon_points": [
          [
            85.0,
            1257.0
          ],
          [
            597.0,
            1257.0
          ],
          [
            597.0,
            1332.0
          ],
          [
            85.0,
            1332.0
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "Training on Different Epochs. Our first goal is to understand how varying training epochs for target and shadow models influence our attacks. We considered two possible scenarios.\n• In the second scenario, the attacker is unaware of the target model's training details and varies only the shadow model's training epochs for experimentation.",
        "block_bbox": [
          85,
          1336,
          598,
          1412
        ],
        "block_id": 13,
        "block_order": 6,
        "group_id": 13,
        "global_block_id": 176,
        "global_group_id": 176,
        "block_polygon_points": [
          [
            85.0,
