          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "Sampling Frequency Variation Analysis. In both GSA₁ and GSA₂, the term 'sample times' (|K|) refers to the number of elements in the set K, derived through the equidistant sampling of timesteps from T. GSA₁ and GSA₂ employ statistical methods on distinct pieces of information; the former determines the mean loss over the |K| timesteps, while the latter computes the average gradient value. Our initial hypothesis was that an increased number of sampling instances, providing the attack model with more information and potentially capturing distinct timesteps that clearly",
